<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n34011c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34011c">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34011c"> 11(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abdul Hamid</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The patriarch Constantine V. was deposed on the 12th of April 1901, and was succeeded on the 28th of May by <mark>Joachim III.</mark> (and V.), who had previously occupied the patriarchal throne from 1878 to 1884, when he was deposed through the ill-will of the Porte and banished to Mount Athos &hellip; His progressive sympathies &hellip; were not very well received, and in 1905 an attempt was made to depose him. The sultan Abd-ul-Hamid, to whom the different parties appealed, lectured them on charity and concord! <small> &ldquo;ORTHODOX EASTERN CHURCH&rdquo; <a name="EBOEC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBOEC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 338 [The Nine National Churches]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
